<title>USA: Onewave sees Q4 revs down from year-ago.</title>
<headline>Onewave sees Q4 revs down from year-ago.</headline>
<dateline>WATERTOWN, Mass. 1997-01-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>OneWave Inc said Monday it expects total revenue for the quarter ended December 31 to be about $2.0 to $2.5 million, down from $3.027 million in the year-ago fourth quarter.</p>
<p>&quot;While we are disappointed by our fourth quarter performance, we are taking this opportunity to re-focus our business efforts,&quot; company Chief Executive Klaus Besier said in a release.</p>
<p>The supplier of Web-enabling software and services said it would report fourth quarter and fiscal year results in the first half of February.</p>
